Senate Resolution 36
By: Senators Halpern of the 39th, Goodman of the 8th, Jones II of the 22nd, Rhett of the
33rd, Orrock of the 36th and others
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing January 27, 2025, as International Holocaust Remembrance Day in the State of
2 Georgia and reaffirming the commitment to combat antisemitism; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, January 27, 2025, marks the 80th anniversary of the liberation of
4 Auschwitz-Birkenau, the largest and most notorious Nazi concentration and extermination
5 camp, where approximately 1.1 million men, women, and children were systematically
6 murdered; and
7 WHEREAS, International Holocaust Remembrance Day is a solemn occasion to honor the
8 six million Jews and millions of other innocent victims who perished during the Holocaust,
9 while also serving as a reminder of the enduring need to confront hatred, bigotry, and
10 antisemitism; and
11 WHEREAS, antisemitism is on the rise globally, including in the State of Georgia, where
12 Jewish communities have faced growing incidents of hate and discrimination; and
13 WHEREAS, on October 7, 2023, the Jewish people endured the deadliest attack against them
14 since the Holocaust by the terrorist organization Hamas while peacefully living in their
